Description:
Now present on 5 continents, LCI Education Network has 23 post-secondary campuses and approximately 3000 employees who educate more than 17,000 students worldwide each year.
We are looking for a .Net Sitecore Developer who will oversee the creation and modification of the functionality in our various web applications. They will collaborate in solution testing, planning, analysis, design conception and construction.
As a more senior resource, they will also handle the more complex issues and act as a mentor to the junior resources on the team.
RESPONSIBILITIES
Design and implement new components or enhancements to existing ones;
Work alongside analysts, architects and software engineers to define and deliver quality technical solutions that meet the requirements;
Work in an independent, dynamic, Scrum / PMP-oriented environment;
Act as a mentor and share knowledge with the team;
Find solutions to the most complex problems:
Recognize and adapt to frequent changes in priorities and direction as business is constantly evolving.
QUALIFICATIONS
Advanced skills in CMS Sitecore and/or WordPress development;
Thorough knowledge of .NET (C #) and Web technologies (JavaScript, CSS, Bootstrap, etc.);
Strong knowledge of SQL;
Experience in intergrading API REST / SOAP;
Ability to solve complex problems;
Ability to collaborate, communicate, learn and transfer knowledge;
Knowledge of SSIS and SSRS an asset.
Minimum of 5 years experience with software development (.Net and MS SQL);
College Studies or Bachelor of Science certification, Computer Option or related field;
Sitecore Knowledge;
Bilingualism in oral and written form (French and English).
BENEFITS
Unlimited online technical training using leading technology platforms;
Certification exams refund (under certain conditions);
International company established for more than 50 years;
Network constantly growing;
Daycare in the workplace;
Regular (permanent) full-time position;
Collective insurance;
Retirement Savings Plan;
Company located in downtown Montreal; the .Net Developer is based in Montreal.
Organization located in downtown Montreal; the .Net Developer is therefore based in Montreal, at 1400 du Fort Street.
You want to contribute to innovative projects in collaboration with teams from all sectors? Do you dream of working for a Quebec-based company with an international scope? Do you want to join a diversified and humane team that looks to the future? What are you waiting for?
Please note that only selected candidates will be contacted. To lighten the text, we follow the rule that allows the masculine gender to be used with the value of neutral. We subscribe to an equal access program.

